reviewText: I didn't really know what to expect from this one, but I know Cenac from his work on the DAILY SHOW, so I decided to give it a try.  I am so glad that I did.  His set on Comedy Person starts off a little slow, but once he gets his rhythm, its really good.  I found myself laughing so hard that I almost spat out my drink (a few times).  I can't wait to hear more from him.  I hope he finds great success, because he's damn funny.
He was so funny!! I've listened to his shows before but watching one was even better!!! Fantastic show!!
Extremely funny comedy show and great picture quality
A sort of unique entertainer and very much worth watching.  There were small stretches where it was not funny to me.
I'm crazy about Wyatt Cenac as a comedian. Wish he would produce more shows on DVD or for streaming.
Hands down, favorite stand up routine ever! It's his monotone delivery of jokes that adds the punch to his realistic views and stories of life.

I was delighted to find this DVD after having seen Wyatt Cenac performing live in NYC. He is a brilliantly funny (if understated) comedian. If you only know him from the Daily Show, be prepared to be blown away! His humor challenges your preconceptions without being 'in your face'. He subtly winds his way into your psyche until you are both intellectually stimulated and laughing your bleeding head off. If you're looking for a raunchy, ni**a a minute routine, keep looking. If you're looking for comedy that stands up to repeated viewing and gets /better/ the more you think about it, grab this DVD. It's a brilliant and insightful look into life, love, race and box-jumping cats.
